{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Every JavaScript object has a hidden "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "[[Prototype]]",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " slot pointing to another object. When you access a property that doesn't exist on the object itself, the engine follows this chain upward until it finds the property or reaches "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "null",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". This mechanism \u2014 the prototype chain \u2014 is how JavaScript implements inheritance, and it is what the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " keyword desugars into."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Prototype chain: runtime lookup, ES5 constructor functions vs ES2015 class syntax, inspection, and mixins",
          "title": "Prototype chain: runtime lookup, ES5 constructor functions vs ES2015 class syntax, inspection, and mixins"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The [[Prototype]] Slot"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Every object created in JavaScript has a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "[[Prototype]]",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " internal slot. It is not directly accessible but can be read and set through specific APIs."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "const animal = { breathes: true };\nconst dog = Object.create(animal);   // dog.[[Prototype]] = animal\ndog.name = 'Rex';\n\ndog.name;       // 'Rex'   \u2014 own property\ndog.breathes;   // true    \u2014 found on animal via prototype chain\ndog.toString;   // function \u2014 found on Object.prototype\n\n// Inspect the chain\nObject.getPrototypeOf(dog) === animal;  // true\n\n// null prototype \u2014 no inherited methods at all\nconst bare = Object.create(null);\nbare.key = 'value';\n// bare.toString  // undefined \u2014 no Object.prototype\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The chain ends at null"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Every ordinary object's chain eventually reaches "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Object.prototype",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (which has "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "toString",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "hasOwnProperty",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", etc.), and then "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "null",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". The lookup stops there."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "const obj = {};\n// obj \u2192 Object.prototype \u2192 null\n\nObject.getPrototypeOf(Object.prototype);  // null\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Constructor Functions (ES5)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Before classes, JavaScript used constructor functions \u2014 regular functions called with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "new",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "new",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " operator creates a fresh object, sets its "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "[[Prototype]]",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to the function's "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ".prototype",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " property, runs the function with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "this",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " pointing to that object, and returns it."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function Animal(name: string) {\n  this.name = name;            // own property\n}\n\n// Methods placed on the prototype \u2014 shared across all instances\nAnimal.prototype.speak = function() {\n  return `${this.name} makes a sound`;\n};\n\nconst cat = new Animal('Whiskers');\ncat.speak();   // \"Whiskers makes a sound\"\n\n// cat.[[Prototype]] === Animal.prototype\n// Animal.prototype.[[Prototype]] === Object.prototype\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Inheriting with ES5"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "function Dog(name: string, breed: string) {\n  Animal.call(this, name);       // call super-constructor to set own properties\n  this.breed = breed;\n}\n\n// Wire the prototype chain\nDog.prototype = Object.create(Animal.prototype);\nDog.prototype.constructor = Dog;\n\nDog.prototype.bark = function() {\n  return `${this.name} barks`;\n};\n\nconst rex = new Dog('Rex', 'Lab');\nrex.bark();    // \"Rex barks\"\nrex.speak();   // \"Rex makes a sound\" \u2014 found on Animal.prototype\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This pattern is verbose and error-prone. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " keyword (ES2015) is syntactic sugar that produces exactly this prototype structure, with none of the boilerplate."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ES2015 Classes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Classes are a cleaner syntax for the same prototype-based inheritance. They are "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "not",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " a different object model \u2014 every class compiles to constructor functions and prototype assignments at runtime."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class Animal {\n  name: string;\n\n  constructor(name: string) {\n    this.name = name;\n  }\n\n  speak(): string {\n    return `${this.name} makes a sound`;\n  }\n}\n\nclass Dog extends Animal {\n  breed: string;\n\n  constructor(name: string, breed: string) {\n    super(name);          // MUST call super() before using this\n    this.breed = breed;\n  }\n\n  bark(): string {\n    return `${this.name} barks`;\n  }\n\n  // Override parent method\n  speak(): string {\n    return `${this.name} barks loudly`;\n  }\n\n  // Call parent version explicitly\n  speakQuietly(): string {\n    return super.speak();\n  }\n}\n\nconst rex = new Dog('Rex', 'Lab');\nrex instanceof Dog;     // true\nrex instanceof Animal;  // true\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method resolution order"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class C extends B {}  // B extends A\n// Instance of C: lookup order is C.prototype \u2192 B.prototype \u2192 A.prototype \u2192 Object.prototype \u2192 null\n\n// Own property always wins over prototype\nclass Greeter {\n  greet() { return 'generic'; }\n}\n\nconst g = new Greeter();\ng.greet = () => 'custom';   // shadow the prototype method\ng.greet();   // 'custom'    \u2014 own property wins\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Static Members"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Static methods and properties belong to the class itself, not to instances. They are attached to the constructor function, not to its "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ".prototype",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class MathUtils {\n  static readonly PI = 3.14159;\n\n  static circleArea(r: number): number {\n    return MathUtils.PI * r * r;\n  }\n\n  // Static factory method \u2014 common pattern\n  static fromDegrees(deg: number): MathUtils {\n    return new MathUtils();\n  }\n}\n\nMathUtils.PI;               // 3.14159\nMathUtils.circleArea(5);    // 78.53975\n\n// Static members are inherited by subclasses\nclass AdvancedMath extends MathUtils {}\nAdvancedMath.PI;            // 3.14159\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Inspecting Prototypes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "API",
                        "marks": [
                          {
                            "type": "bold"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "What it does",
                        "marks": [
                          {
                            "type": "bold"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "obj instanceof Cls"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "true if Cls.prototype is anywhere in obj's chain"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Object.getPrototypeOf(obj)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "returns obj's [[Prototype]] (null for Object.prototype)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Object.hasOwn(obj, key)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "true only if key is an own property (not inherited)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "obj.constructor"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "usually points back to the constructor function (can be overridden)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Object.create(proto)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "creates object with proto as its [[Prototype]]"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Reflect.getPrototypeOf(obj)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "attrs": {},
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "same as getPrototypeOf, from Reflect API"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class Vehicle { wheels = 4; }\nclass Car extends Vehicle { doors = 4; }\n\nconst car = new Car();\n\ncar instanceof Car;                          // true\ncar instanceof Vehicle;                      // true\n\nObject.hasOwn(car, 'wheels');                // true (own \u2014 set by constructor)\nObject.hasOwn(car, 'toString');              // false (on Object.prototype)\n\nObject.getPrototypeOf(car) === Car.prototype;         // true\nObject.getPrototypeOf(Car.prototype) === Vehicle.prototype;  // true\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mixins \u2014 Composition over Deep Inheritance"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Deep class hierarchies are brittle. Mixins let you compose independent behaviours by applying them as class factories."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// A mixin is a function that takes a base class and returns an extended class\ntype Constructor<T = {}> = new (...args: any[]) => T;\n\nfunction Serializable<TBase extends Constructor>(Base: TBase) {\n  return class extends Base {\n    serialize(): string {\n      return JSON.stringify(this);\n    }\n    static deserialize<T>(json: string): T {\n      return JSON.parse(json) as T;\n    }\n  };\n}\n\nfunction Timestamped<TBase extends Constructor>(Base: TBase) {\n  return class extends Base {\n    createdAt = new Date();\n    updatedAt = new Date();\n  };\n}\n\nclass User {\n  constructor(public name: string) {}\n}\n\n// Compose without a hierarchy\nconst TimestampedSerializableUser = Serializable(Timestamped(User));\nconst user = new TimestampedSerializableUser('Deiva');\nuser.serialize();    // JSON of name + timestamps\nuser.createdAt;      // Date object\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prototypes in Angular"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Angular components and services are TypeScript classes. Their Angular-specific behaviours (lifecycle hooks, dependency injection, change detection) are wired by the framework using the same prototype system."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Lifecycle hooks via inheritance"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Base class with shared lifecycle logic\nabstract class DestroyableComponent implements OnDestroy {\n  protected destroy$ = new Subject<void>();\n\n  ngOnDestroy() {\n    this.destroy$.next();\n    this.destroy$.complete();\n  }\n}\n\n// Subclass inherits destroy$ and ngOnDestroy\n@Component({ selector: 'app-user-list', template: '' })\nexport class UserListComponent extends DestroyableComponent implements OnInit {\n  users: User[] = [];\n\n  constructor(private userService: UserService) { super(); }\n\n  ngOnInit() {\n    this.userService.getUsers().pipe(\n      takeUntil(this.destroy$),    // inherited from base\n    ).subscribe(u => this.users = u);\n  }\n}\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Service inheritance"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "abstract class BaseApiService {\n  protected baseUrl = '/api';\n\n  constructor(protected http: HttpClient) {}\n\n  protected handleError(err: HttpErrorResponse): Observable<never> {\n    console.error('API error:', err.message);\n    return throwError(() => err);\n  }\n}\n\n@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })\nexport class UserApiService extends BaseApiService {\n  constructor(http: HttpClient) { super(http); }\n\n  getUsers(): Observable<User[]> {\n    return this.http.get<User[]>(`${this.baseUrl}/users`).pipe(\n      catchError(this.handleError.bind(this))\n    );\n  }\n}\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Forgetting super() in a subclass constructor \u2014 JavaScript throws a ReferenceError before this is accessible"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Adding methods to an instance instead of the prototype \u2014 every instance gets its own copy, wasting memory"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Over-using inheritance \u2014 prefer composition (mixins, services) for shared behaviour; deep hierarchies are hard to refactor"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Mutating Object.prototype \u2014 affects every object in the runtime; never do this"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Confusing instanceof with duck typing \u2014 instanceof checks the prototype chain, not the shape; use type guards for structural checks"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Private Fields with # (ES2022)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "TypeScript's "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "private",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " keyword is compile-time only \u2014 the property is fully accessible at runtime via JavaScript. True private fields use the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "#",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " prefix, which is enforced at the JavaScript engine level."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class BankAccount {\n  #balance: number;   // truly private \u2014 inaccessible outside the class\n\n  constructor(initial: number) {\n    this.#balance = initial;\n  }\n\n  deposit(amount: number) {\n    if (amount <= 0) throw new RangeError('amount must be positive');\n    this.#balance += amount;\n  }\n\n  get balance() { return this.#balance; }\n}\n\nconst acc = new BankAccount(100);\nacc.deposit(50);\nacc.balance;   // 150\n\n// acc.#balance;     // SyntaxError \u2014 not accessible\n// (acc as any)['#balance'];  // undefined \u2014 not even in the object map\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "private vs # comparison"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class A {\n  private tsPrivate = 1;   // TypeScript only \u2014 removed at compile time\n  #jsPrivate = 2;           // JavaScript engine enforced\n\n  demo() {\n    console.log(this.tsPrivate);  // OK\n    console.log(this.#jsPrivate); // OK\n  }\n}\n\nconst a = new A();\n(a as any).tsPrivate;   // 1  \u2014 accessible at runtime (TypeScript erased)\n// a.#jsPrivate;         // SyntaxError \u2014 blocked by the engine\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Abstract Classes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Abstract classes cannot be instantiated directly \u2014 they define a contract that subclasses must implement. Useful for shared base behaviour with enforced interface."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "abstract class Shape {\n  abstract area(): number;         // must be implemented by subclasses\n  abstract perimeter(): number;\n\n  // Concrete method shared by all shapes\n  describe(): string {\n    return `Area: ${this.area().toFixed(2)}, Perimeter: ${this.perimeter().toFixed(2)}`;\n  }\n}\n\nclass Circle extends Shape {\n  constructor(private radius: number) { super(); }\n  area() { return Math.PI * this.radius ** 2; }\n  perimeter() { return 2 * Math.PI * this.radius; }\n}\n\nclass Rectangle extends Shape {\n  constructor(private w: number, private h: number) { super(); }\n  area() { return this.w * this.h; }\n  perimeter() { return 2 * (this.w + this.h); }\n}\n\n// new Shape();  // Error: Cannot create an instance of an abstract class\nconst c = new Circle(5);\nc.describe();   // \"Area: 78.54, Perimeter: 31.42\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prototype Methods Added Dynamically"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prototype properties can be added or replaced after a class is defined. This is rarely desirable in TypeScript code, but it helps explain why polyfills work \u2014 they add missing methods to built-in prototypes before your code runs."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// Polyfill example: add a method to Array.prototype if the engine lacks it\nif (!Array.prototype.at) {\n  Object.defineProperty(Array.prototype, 'at', {\n    value: function(index: number) {\n      return index >= 0 ? this[index] : this[this.length + index];\n    },\n    writable: true,\n    configurable: true,\n    enumerable: false,   // don't show up in for...in\n  });\n}\n\n// Avoid this pattern in your own code \u2014 mutating built-in prototypes\n// conflicts with other libraries or future language additions\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prototype vs. Own Property Performance"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Methods defined in the class body go on the prototype \u2014 they are created once and shared by all instances. Methods defined as arrow class fields go on the instance \u2014 each "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "new",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " call creates a separate function object."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class WithProtoMethod {\n  greet() { return 'hello'; }         // prototype \u2014 one function object for all instances\n}\n\nclass WithArrowField {\n  greet = () => 'hello';              // own \u2014 new function per instance\n}\n\n// Implication: 10000 instances of WithArrowField create 10000 function objects\n// Implication: 10000 instances of WithProtoMethod share 1 function object\n\n// When to use arrow fields anyway:\n// - When the method is passed as a callback (to avoid context loss)\n// - Event handlers in Angular components: onClick = () => this.doWork()\n//   \u2192 this is always the component; no bind() needed\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "JavaScript inheritance is prototype-based: every object has a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "[[Prototype]]",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " link, and property lookups walk this chain. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " syntax is sugar over constructor functions and prototype assignments \u2014 the runtime model is identical. Angular components and services use standard class inheritance; lifecycle hooks are just methods resolved through the prototype chain. For shared behaviour, prefer flat mixins over deep hierarchies."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}